Create a Shift Segment Type

A shift segment type represents an activity thatâ€™s performed by an agent during the workday. A segment type can be a work activity (chat, email, or phone call), non-work activity (meeting or training), or break (break or lunch). In Workforce Engagement, a shift segment type can also specify an adherence threshold to help ensure that agents are working on the correct assignment.

Workforce Engagement is available in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Shift Scheduling is available in the Contact Center Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), Einstein 1 Service Edition, and Service Suites.

To view, create, and edit shifts and shift segments: 
Shift Scheduling
OR 
Workforce Engagement Planner

Steps for Omni-Channel Queue-Based Routing Customers:
From Setup, search for and select Shift Segment Types.
Click New.
Name your shift segment type.
Select a category (Work, Non-Work, Break).
Select a service presence status.
Select an adherence threshold (if using Workforce Engagement).

Steps for Shift Scheduling or Workforce Engagement Without Omni-Channel:
From Setup, search for and select Shift Segment Types.
Click New.
Name your shift segment type.
Select a category (Work, Non-Work, Break).
(If using Workforce Engagement) Select an adherence threshold.

After creating the shift segment types, add them to shift segments that can be assigned to an agent.
title: Shift Segment Types in Service Cloud
